03/11/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- Top Albanian, Kosovo Albanian and Macedonian Albanian officials met in Tirana Saturday (2 November) to discuss greater involvement of Albanians in European institutions. 
Among those attending were Prime Minister Fatos Nano, Albanian officials in Kosovo Adem Demaci, Albin Kurti and the head of the Albanian Democratic Party in Macedonia Arben Xhaferri. 
They agreed that Albanian communities should encourage progress in adopting democratic standards to initiate regional integration processes with the rest of Europe. 
(ATA - 02/11/02)
